    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nAn edge case with the walrus operator + raise inside try/except doesn't compile. I am porting existing tested production code to cython and found a subset of walrus operators could not compile due to this issue\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\nasync def fails_in_try():\n    \"\"\"\n    Error on line 34: local variable 'x' referenced before assignment\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        if not (x := await get_value()):\n            raise ValueError(\"Not found\")\n\n        return x[\"key\"]  # <-- Cython thinks x might be unassigned\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nNo error should be raised.\n\n### OS\n\nUbuntu 25.10\n\n### Python version\n\nPython 3.13\n\n### Cython version\n\nCython 3.2.4\n\n### Additional context\n\n```python\n# =============================================================================\n# WORKS: Same pattern outside try/except\n# =============================================================================\nasync def works_outside_try():\n    \"\"\"This compiles fine - Cython correctly tracks the raise terminates flow.\"\"\"\n    if not (x := await get_value()):\n        raise ValueError(\"Not found\")\n\n    return x[\"key\"]  # <-- Cython knows x is assigned here\n\n\n# =============================================================================\n# WORKS: Separate assignment from condition workaround\n# =============================================================================\nasync def workaround():\n    \"\"\"Separating assignment from condition works around the bug.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        x = await get_value()\n        if not x:\n            raise ValueError(\"Not found\")\n\n        return x[\"key\"]\n    except Exception:\n        pass\n```",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-13T17:17:15Z",
